ðŸ” Learn Git commands: clone, branch, merge, pull request, revert

ðŸ§© Phase 4: Build Pipelines (CI)
âœ… Classic Pipeline (GUI):

Go to Pipelines â†’ Create Pipeline â†’ Use Classic Editor

Select Repo â†’ Choose agent (e.g., Ubuntu)

Add Tasks:

Install dependencies

Build (e.g., Maven, .NET, npm)

Publish artifacts

âœ… YAML Pipeline (Code-based):

yaml
Copy
Edit
trigger:
  - main

pool:
  vmImage: 'ubuntu-latest'

steps:
- script: echo "Building project"
- script: dotnet build
- script: dotnet test
âœ… Push azure-pipelines.yml to repo

ðŸ§© Phase 5: Release Pipelines (CD)
Go to Releases

Create a new release pipeline

Add Artifact â†’ from build pipeline

Add Stages (e.g., Dev, QA, Prod)

Add tasks: Copy files, Deploy to VM, AKS, App Service

Enable approvals and gates

ðŸ§© Phase 6: Infrastructure as Code (IaC)
âœ… Integrate Terraform, ARM/Bicep, or Ansible:

yaml
Copy
Edit
